{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a native SwiftUI API on top of FlyHUD’s UIKit core. It offers four levels of abstraction:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Layer"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Case"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bridge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":".hudHost($hostView)","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Direct UIKit-style control","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Declarative"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hud(isPresented:)"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hud(item:)"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".hudStatus(isPresented:)","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Binding-driven state management"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Convenience"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudLoading()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudToast()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudProgress()"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Common presets with minimal setup","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Liquid Glass"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudGlass()"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS 26+ translucent glass style","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All APIs support iOS 13+, tvOS 13+, and visionOS 1.0+."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Architecture","anchor":"Architecture","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following diagram shows the layered architecture and how each public API flows through internal components to the UIKit core:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"swiftui-architecture.svg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"How It Works","anchor":"How-It-Works","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following diagram shows the interaction flow between SwiftUI bindings and the UIKit HUD:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"swiftui-bridge.svg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Installation","anchor":"Installation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" to your package dependencies:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/liam-i\/FlyHUD.git\", from: \"1.7.0\")","],","targets: [","    .target(","        name: \"MyTarget\",","        dependencies: [","            .product(name: \"FlyHUDSwiftUI\", package: \"FlyHUD\")","        ]","    )","]"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Or in Xcode: File → Add Package Dependencies → select ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" depends on "},{"code":"FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically. You only need to add "},{"code":"FlyIndicatorHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"FlyProgressHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if you use custom indicator\/progress styles."}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Import","text":"Import"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import FlyHUDSwiftUI","","\/\/ Optional — for custom indicator styles","import FlyIndicatorHUD","","\/\/ Optional — for custom progress styles","import FlyProgressHUD"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Layer-1-UIKit-Bridge","text":"Layer 1: UIKit Bridge"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For maximum control, use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudHost()"},{"type":"text","text":" to obtain a backing UIView, then call UIKit APIs directly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct MyView: View {","    @State private var hostView: UIView?","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Button(\"Show HUD\") {","                guard let view = hostView else { return }","                HUD.show(to: view, mode: .indicator(), label: \"Loading...\")","            }","            Button(\"Hide HUD\") {","                guard let view = hostView else { return }","                HUD.hide(for: view)","            }","        }","        .hudHost($hostView)","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This pattern gives you full access to the HUD instance and all configuration options.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Layer-2-Declarative-Modifiers","type":"heading","text":"Layer 2: Declarative Modifiers"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Boolean-Driven-HUD","type":"heading","text":"Boolean-Driven HUD"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Toggle a HUD by binding a Boolean:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct DownloadView: View {","    @State private var isLoading = false","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Download\") {","            isLoading = true","            startDownload { isLoading = false }","        }","        .hud(isPresented: $isLoading) { hud in","            hud.contentView.mode = .indicator()","            hud.contentView.label.text = \"Downloading...\"","        }","    }","}"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Item-Driven-HUD","type":"heading","text":"Item-Driven HUD"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Present different HUD states based on an ","type":"text"},{"code":"Identifiable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" item:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["struct HUDItem: Identifiable {","    let id = UUID()","    let mode: ContentView.Mode","    let label: String","}","","struct TaskView: View {","    @State private var hudItem: HUDItem?","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Start\") {","            hudItem = HUDItem(mode: .indicator(), label: \"Working...\")","        }","        .hud(item: $hudItem) { item, hud in","            hud.contentView.mode = item.mode","            hud.contentView.label.text = item.label","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Self-Dismissing-Status","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Self-Dismissing Status"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Show a toast that automatically hides after a duration:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct SaveView: View {","    @State private var showSaved = false","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Save\") {","            save()","            showSaved = true","        }","        .hudStatus(isPresented: $showSaved, duration: 2.0) { hud in","            hud.contentView.mode = .text","            hud.contentView.label.text = \"Saved!\"","        }","    }","}"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Layer-3-Convenience-Presets","type":"heading","text":"Layer 3: Convenience Presets"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Loading-Indicator","type":"heading","text":"Loading Indicator"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["MyView()","    .hudLoading(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Please wait...\")"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Toast-Message","type":"heading","text":"Toast Message"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["MyView()","    .hudToast(isPresented: $showToast, duration: 1.5, label: \"File deleted\")"]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Progress-Tracking","type":"heading","text":"Progress Tracking"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct UploadView: View {","    @State private var isUploading = false","    @State private var progress: Float = 0","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Upload\") { startUpload() }","            .hudProgress(isPresented: $isUploading, progress: $progress, label: \"Uploading\")","    }","}"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Layer-4-Liquid-Glass-iOS-26+","type":"heading","text":"Layer 4: Liquid Glass (iOS 26+)"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On iOS 26 and later, use the glass style for a modern translucent appearance:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["MyView()","    .hudGlass(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Loading...\")"]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":".hudGlass()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is only available when compiling with Swift 6.2+ and targeting iOS 26.0 or tvOS 26.0.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Animation-Customization","type":"heading","text":"Animation Customization"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All declarative modifiers accept an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"animation"},{"text":" parameter:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":[".hud(isPresented: $isLoading, animation: .init(.zoomInOut, damping: .default)) { hud in","    hud.contentView.mode = .indicator()","}"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Migration-from-UIKit-Bridge","type":"heading","text":"Migration from UIKit Bridge"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you previously used a local ","type":"text"},{"code":"HUDHostView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" helper, you can now:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"import FlyHUD"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"import FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remove your local "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUDHostView"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUDContainerModifier"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"code":"hudHost()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" definitions","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudHost($hostView)"},{"text":" API is now provided by the SDK","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For new code, prefer the declarative modifiers (Layer 2\/3) over ","type":"text"},{"code":".hudHost()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for cleaner state management.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Best-Practices","text":"Best Practices"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"One HUD per view hierarchy","type":"text"}]},{"text":" — Avoid attaching multiple ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hud()"},{"text":" modifiers to the same view. Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"item:"},{"text":" variant for multiple states.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Set binding to "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on dismissal"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" — The status modifier does this automatically, but for ","type":"text"},{"code":".hud(isPresented:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" you must reset the binding yourself.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Combine with "},{"code":"FlyIndicatorHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyProgressHUD"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Custom styles work the same way; just pass them via the configuration closure."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Prefer convenience presets","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" — Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudLoading()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudToast()"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudProgress()"},{"type":"text","text":" for common cases to reduce boilerplate."}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/flyhud\/swiftui-integration"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use FlyHUD declaratively in SwiftUI with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" module."}],"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"FlyHUD"}],"title":"SwiftUI Integration","roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/advanced-features","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/custom-ui","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/best-practices","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/testing"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/swiftui-integration"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"references":{"swiftui-bridge.svg":{"alt":"Sequence diagram showing how SwiftUI binding changes flow through HUDModifier, HUDRepresentable, and HUDCoordinator to control HUD visibility","identifier":"swiftui-bridge.svg","type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/swiftui-bridge.svg","svgID":"my-svg"}]},"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/testing":{"type":